    <stitle>CF 500, CF 600 Brakes - Parking Brake and Actuation - General Procedures</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
        <title>General Procedures</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Parking Brake Cable Adjustment</title>
            <table id="t0605007">
                <title>Special Tool</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="0.94*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.06*"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <graphic filename="../figST2/ST2814A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="112px"
                                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Gauge, Parking Brake Cable Adjustment</para>
                                <para>ZTSE4569</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Set the parking brake.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Raise and support the vehicle. For additional information, refer to
                    <exhotlnk document="../S10/S10019.htm" bookname="S10019">Jacking and Lifting in S10019</exhotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the parking brake cable adjuster along the RH side frame rail.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Hold the adjuster and loosen the adjuster locknut.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0605007" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024257.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using the special tool, check the parking brake cable tension. Depress the tool handle
                    fully so that the wheel will engage the far side of the cable.
                </para>
                <para>Release the handle quickly but smoothly and read the direct tension units on the dial face next to
                    the indicating bar.
                </para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Correct cable tension for adjustment of a new cable is 181 kg (400 lb).</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Correct cable tension for adjustment of an existing cable is 181 kg (400 lb).</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0605009" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024259.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If tension is incorrect, remove the tool, release the park brake and readjust the
                    tension by rotating the park brake cable adjuster. Recheck the cable tension. Repeat Steps 1-4 until
                    tension is within specifications.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the adjuster locknut to 24 Nm (18 lb-ft).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Test the parking brake operation.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Parking Brake Cable Tension Release</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Make sure the parking brake control is fully released.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the parking brake cable adjuster along the RH side frame rail.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Hold the adjuster and loosen the adjuster locknut.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0605012" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0024257.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
